    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="403"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2126/399A.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Furniss</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In view of unanimity of Gen. Simon’s election by the national congress, you will
                    forthwith recognize his de facto presidency. Confer with naval commander as to
                    hour of recognition so that salute may be exchanged.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
